    About

    Description

    Earth Day is an annual event on April 22 to demonstrate support for environmental protection. First held on April 22, 1970, it now includes a wide range of events coordinated globally by Earthday.org including 1 billion people in more than 193 countries. The official theme for 2024 is "Planet vs. Plastics." Wikipedia
    Date: Monday, April 22, 2024
    Significance: Support for environmental protection
    ReasonWhy do we celebrate Earth Day?
    WHY DO WE CELEBRATE EARTH DAY? Earth Day has its roots in growing concern over pollution in the 1960s, when author Rachel Carson's 1962 book Silent Spring, about the pesticide DDT and its damaging effects on the food chain, hit bestseller lists and raised awareness about nature's delicate balance.2 hours ago
